<p class="eyebrow">Support / Phone / Poly &amp; Polycom</p>
<h1>Configure Poly / Polycom VVX phones for VoiceTel.</h1>
<p class="lede">VVX 250, 350, 450, and Edge series phones running UC Software 6.x or later use the same Lines tab configuration. Provision via the web UI for individual phones or via Polycom ZTP for fleet rollouts.</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Web UI configuration</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Find the IP address: <strong>Settings → Status → Network → TCP/IP Parameters</strong>.</li>
		<li>Open <code>https://&lt;phone-ip&gt;</code>. Sign in as <strong>Admin</strong> (default password <code>456</code> — change immediately).</li>
		<li>Open <strong>Settings → Lines → Line 1 → Identification</strong>.</li>
		<li>Set:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Display Name:</strong> the user's name</li>
				<li><strong>Address (SIP URI):</strong> <code>sip:&lt;username&gt;@&lt;voicetel-sip-server&gt;</code></li>
				<li><strong>Authentication User ID:</strong> the SIP username from VoiceTel onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Authentication Password:</strong> the SIP password from VoiceTel onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Label:</strong> short label shown on the line key</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Open <strong>Server 1</strong> tab:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Address:</strong> the VoiceTel SIP server host</li>
				<li><strong>Port:</strong> 5060 (or 5061 for TLS)</li>
				<li><strong>Transport:</strong> UDPOnly (or TLS)</li>
				<li><strong>Expires:</strong> 60</li>
				<li><strong>Register:</strong> Yes</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Open <strong>SIP → Local Settings</strong>.</li>
		<li>Set:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>NAT Keep-Alive Interval:</strong> 30</li>
				<li><strong>NAT Keep-Alive Method:</strong> rport (or empty SIP REGISTER)</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Save and reboot.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Codec preference</h2>
	<p>Open <strong>Settings → Codec Profiles → Audio Codec Priority</strong>. Move PCMU and PCMA to positions 1 and 2. Disable G.722 unless onboarding confirmed support. Disable Lync codecs (SIREN/RTAudio) unless deploying with Microsoft.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Auto-provisioning</h2>
	<p>Polycom ZTP (Zero Touch Provisioning) is the equivalent of Yealink RPS:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Register your phone's MAC range in the ZTP portal at <code>https://ztp.poly.com</code>.</li>
		<li>Point ZTP at your VoiceTel provisioning URL.</li>
		<li>Phones contact ZTP at boot, get redirected, fetch their VoiceTel config and register.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>For self-hosted provisioning, the phone boots looking for <code>000000000000.cfg</code> and per-MAC <code>&lt;mac&gt;.cfg</code> files via TFTP/HTTP/HTTPS. Contact engineering for VoiceTel-specific config templates.</p>
</section>

<aside class="cta-block" aria-labelledby="polycom-cta-heading">
	<h2 id="polycom-cta-heading">Phone showing "Registration Failed"?</h2>
	<p>Capture an SIP trace from <strong>Diagnostics → Logs → Application Log</strong> at log level <code>5 (Debug)</code>. Send the log + phone model + firmware version to VoiceTel engineering.</p>
	<p class="hero-actions">
		<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact/">Contact engineering</a>
	</p>
</aside>
